# Reconnaissance - Practical Notes

## Passive Reconnaissance (OSINT)

### Google Dorking
Search for publicly exposed information.

Examples:
```text
site:target.com filetype:pdf
site:target.com ext:sql
site:target.com intitle:"index of"
```

---

### theHarvester
Collect:
- Emails
- Subdomains
- Hostnames

Example:
```bash
theHarvester -d target.com -l 500 -b google
```

---

### Shodan
Search Internet-facing devices.

Examples:
```bash
shodan search org:"Target Organization"
```

Useful for:
- Open ports
- Server banners
- Exposed services
- IoT devices

---

## Active Reconnaissance

### Nmap

#### SYN Scan
```bash
nmap -sS -p- <IP>
```

#### Version Detection
```bash
nmap -sV <IP>
```

#### OS Detection
```bash
nmap -O <IP>
```

#### Common Combination
```bash
nmap -sS -sV -O <IP>
```

---

### Gobuster

Directory enumeration.

Example:
```bash
gobuster dir -u http://target.com -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt
```

Purpose:
- Hidden directories
- Hidden files
- Admin panels
- Backup files

---

